OUR COMPANY 
OVERVIEW
Headquartered in Schaumburg, Illinois, GMC collects upon distressed consumer assets.  GMC’s experienced management team combines technology, creativity and motivated employees to construct client-driven recovery solutions. Whether working as a first-party debt collector or as a third-party contingency collections agency, the management team at Glass Mountain Capital has the solution to your collections maze.  
GMC not only provides liquidity solutions to its business partners, it also strives to work with past-due consumers in a productive manner.  GMC is committed to helping consumers meet their financial obligations.  Treating each person with dignity and respect, GMC tailors payment options to match individual needs and challenges.
GMC maintains a high degree of professionalism and ethics.  GMC adheres to local and federal laws governing debt collections and data privacy.  GMC is proud to be an active member of the following professional collections and asset buying organizations:
ACA International
The Association of Credit and Collection Professionals.
ICA
Illinois Collectors Association.
DBA International
Education. Integrity. Professionalism. 


